Two offices of the Independent National Electoral Commission in Ebonyi State have been set ablaze by unidentified persons. The offices are located in Ebonyi and Ezza North Local Government Areas of the state. It was gathered that no casualties were recorded but there were extensive damages to the building and facilities. The Commission is yet to issue a full statement on the incident. DAILY POST reports that the latest attack brings the number of offices of the Commission that have been torched to 23. This is coming weeks after the commissionâ€™s offices in Akwa Ibom, Abia, Anambra, Enugu and Imo were also razed by unknown hoodlums. INEC office set ablaze in Akwa Ibom 